e pointwise equality, since ∑ zʲ(uⱼ−vⱼ) is degree-≤l with >l roots) + weighting_transfer_double_count (the double count α·|S′| ≤ W(D′)·|S′| + (W_tot−W(D′))·l) + weighting_transfer_bound (µ(D′) ≥ α − l/(|S′|−l)). weighted_agreement_of_coCurvilinear composes it from CoCurvilinearity. ⚑ 07-16 FIX: CoCurvilinearity WAS VACUOUS — it quantified ∃v over ARBITRARY words with the codeword constraint only in a docstring aside, so v:=u proved it outright (coCurvilinearity_unconstrained_is_vacuous) and "discharging" it would have earned ZERO bits. It now carries ∀j≤l, IsRSCodeword pt k (v j), and non-vacuity is PROVED not asserted (coCurvilinearity_has_a_falsifier exhibits a u where it is FALSE). NEW: BCIKS20 Lemma 7.6 MECHANIZED (OnGrid/grid_round/weighting_transfer_rounded) — the grid rounding that removes 7.5's loss, previously only prose; given CoCurvilinearity, FRI's grid weights now yield µ(D′) ≥ α EXACTLY. SCOPE, AUDITED: the public route closes for the DENOMINATOR-BOUNDED weights FRI uses (µ⁽ⁱ⁾ = subtree-acceptance, denominator |D⁰|/|D⁽ⁱ⁺¹⁾| — on the grid, so Lemma 7.6's rounding fires) — NOT for full Cor 4.4's arbitrary real weights (no grid ⟹ Thm 4.3 genuinely needed). THE BITS, HONESTLY: recomputed with the linear ε_C, composed via ethSTARK eq.(20), the deployed wrap moves ~64→~71 (+7), leaf ~70→~72 (+1.7), outer ~66→~71 (+5.5) — NOT the +17…+31 the naive log₂|D⁰| suggested, because once ε_C clears the query column the min in eq.(20) is set by ζ−s·log₂α≈72, and the arity-8 degree-7 CURVE needs multiplicity 2h where the binary line needs h. RESIDUAL (public, no personal comm, but LARGE): mechanize BCI+20 §5.2.5–5.2.7 + Appendix A (Hensel lift over the algebraic function field K[X,Y]/H(X,Y), K=F_q(Z)) PLUS BCSS25 §3.2's improved bookkeeping so Step-4's S′ clears |S′| ≥ (|D⁰|+1)·l. MATHLIB GAP SCOPED: no coding theory AT ALL (no RS/linear codes/distance/Johnson/list-decoding); weightedTotalDegree has a def and 4 lemmas (no _mul_le — the GS degree bound IS that); NO biva